---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 11
  Paragraph: 27
Title: Let It Be, Leave It Alone
---
Cloud Chief said, "I too consider myself a demented drifter, but the
people follow me wherever I go and I have no choice but to think of
them. It is for their sake now that I beg one word of instruction!"
